## Example 2: Municipality specifies several but not all priority fields 

The majority of municipalities in the region fell into this category; their codes specify a few of the fields we collected but not all of them, so we have calculated estimates for those not collected using other specifications in the code. The table of dimensional requirements from the zoning code of one such municipality is below in Image A. This municipality specifies minimum lot size \(`Minimum Lot Area`\), and maximum floor-area-ratio, but not dwelling units allowed per acre. Maximum building height and residential uses are specified in the text of the code. To estimate dwelling units allowed per acre, we calculated the number of lots that could be constructed in an acre and multiplied this number by the maximum number of dwelling units allowed on a lot.
